## No Migration Changes Needed

The workers table already exists in the initial schema (20240101000001_initial_schema.sql) with all needed columns: id, host, labels (JSONB), capabilities (JSONB), client_version, last_seen_at, created_at. No new migration required.

## Architecture Notes

- All worker routes are behind API key auth (same middleware as other authenticated routes)
- Staleness is computed on read, not via background task (per spec)
- Version check uses compile-time `CARGO_PKG_VERSION` from server's Cargo.toml (0.1.0)
- Labels stored as JSONB array in DB, serialized/deserialized via serde_json
- Job reclamation on worker delete only affects jobs with status='running'
- The `compute_connection_status` function is reusable for task pull (Task 10)
